NOTES:
Chapter One:
- There are 3 types of IP addresses. The type affects how forwarding is performed
  - Unicast: Destined for a single host
  - Broadcast: Destined for all hosts on a given network
  - Multicast: Destined for a set of hosts that belong to a multicast group
- ICMP is used by the IP layer to exchange error messages with the IP layer in
another host or router
  - Ping and traceroute utilize ICMP
  - ICMP messages are encapsulated within IP datagrams in the same way
transport layer PDUs are 
